Class FilterDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.app.Fragment
      • android.app.DialogFragment
        • com.boyanstoynov.littlebigspender.main.transactions.FilterDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.app.DatePickerDialog.OnDateSetListener, android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.content.DialogInterface.OnCancelListener, android.content.DialogInterface.OnDismissListener, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener

    public class FilterDialog
extends android.app.DialogFragment
implements android.app.DatePickerDialog.OnDateSetListener
    Filter dialog to select a filter for a list of transactions. Displays radio buttons which enable their input and disable the others, allowing only one type of filter to be applied. Also has a button to reset the filter applied. Provides callback to the listener upon selection of a filter.
    Author:
    Boyan Stoynov
